{"title_page": "Nguoi Viet Daily News", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=May 2017}}\n{{infobox newspaper\n| name                 = Ng\u01b0\u1eddi Vi\u1ec7t\n| logo                 = \n| image                = Nguoi_Viet_News.jpg\n| caption              = Ng\u01b0\u1eddi Vi\u1ec7t Daily News Head Quarter\n| type                 = [[Daily newspaper]]\n| format               = Print, Digital, Online, Video, Social Media\n| status               = Active\n| owners               = ESOP\n| founder              = \u0110\u1ed7 Ng\u1ecdc Y\u1ebfn\n| publisher            = \u0110\u1ed7 Qu\u00fd To\u00e0n\n| assistant to the publisher               = \u0110inh Quang Anh Th\u00e1i\n| Chief Executive Officer                = \u0110\u1ed7 B\u1ea3o Anh\n| Chief Editor          = \u0110\u1ed7 Qu\u00fd To\u00e0n\n| Online News Editor    = Kh\u00f4i Nguy\u00ean\n| Staff Writers         = Ng\u1ecdc Lan, Nh\u1ea5t Anh, Qu\u1ed1c D\u0169ng, Titi Tr\u1ea7n, Nguy\u00ean Huy, Ph\u1ea1m Qu\u1ed1c B\u1ea3o, L\u1ed9c Nguy\u1ec5n, H\u00e0 Giang, Vi\u1ec7t Linh, H\u00e0 T\u01b0\u1eddng C\u00e1t, Du T\u1eed L\u00ea, Phan Thanh Tuy\u1ec1n, Huy Ph\u01b0\u01a1ng, D\u00e2n Hu\u1ef3nh, \u0110\u1ed7 Dz\u0169ng, \u0110\u1ea7ng Giao, Khoa L\u1ea1i\n| Art Director          = \u00c1nh B\u00f9i\n| Sales Director        = Vicky Ho\u00e0ng V\u0129nh\n| Online Business Development          = V\u0169 Qu\u1ed1c B\u1ea3o\n| Accounting / Finance Exec. VP = Tr\u1ea7n \u0110\u1ee9c Long\n| IT Manager         = Shawn Long Nguy\u1ec5n\n| CIO/Technology Advisor          = Phan Huy Quang\n| staff                = \n| foundation           = December 15, 1978\n| language             = {{in lang|vi|en}}\n| ceased publication   = \n| headquarters         = [[Westminster, California]]\n| subsidiary           = \n| circulation          = 9,956 (July 1, 2015 - June 30, 2016) - Verified Audit Circulation\n| sister newspapers    = Saigon Nh\u1ecf (Little Saigon News)\n| website              = http://www.nguoi-viet.com/\n}}\n'''''Nguoi Viet Daily News, Inc.''''' ({{lang-vi|Nh\u1eadt b\u00e1o Ng\u01b0\u1eddi Vi\u1ec7t}}) is the first, oldest, and largest daily newspaper published in [[Vietnamese language|Vietnamese]] outside of mainland Vietnam. The story of the newspaper is an American Dream success story.  The newspaper was established by husband and wife [[Yen Ngoc Do and Loan La Do]] in 1978, three years after escaping the Vietnam War with their family. Yen had served as a journalist during the Vietnam War, and wrote for such prestigious outlets as the Rand Corporation based in California. Loan had risen to become a well-known English school teacher after graduating from college. During the Vietnam War, Yen and Loan were one of the few married Vietnamese couples who were each fluent in English, and could readily communicate across the spectrum of individuals - Vietnamese, American, and others - involved in fighting the communists. Therefore, they garnered a vast following from people who were hungry for the news. The name of their newspaper ''ng\u01b0\u1eddi Vi\u1ec7t'' symbolizes [[Vietnamese people]]\".<ref name=\"Yen Do and the Story of Nguoi Viet Daily News\">{{cite web|publisher= maxreading|title=Yen Do and the Story of Nguoi Viet Daily News |url= https://www.amazon.com/Story-Nguoi-Viet-Daily-News/dp/1629880248}}</ref>\n\n''Nguoi Viet Daily News'' began as a weekly four-page newspaper.<ref name=\"LAT 2019-03-21\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-col1-viet-newspaper-20190321-htmlstory.html|title=In Little Saigon, this newspaper has been giving a community a voice for 40 years|last=Do|first=Anh|date=March 21, 2019|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref> The first issue, dated December 15, 1978, was printed in the couple's garage in Orange County, California, with the assistance of their entire family consisting of four extremely young children.  Just as the story of the newspaper is an American Dream success story - the story of entrepreneurship (especially made famous by California garages) started in Southern California long before the rise of Silicon Valley.  The Do family's blood, sweat, and tears catalyzed and financed the initial press run of 2,000 copies with $4,000 of their own life savings from their Vietnam War escape.\n\nThe first edition of \"Nguoi Viet Daily News\" was a four-page publication, printed and distributed on December 15, 1978, in San Diego, California. After operating as a weekly for some time, the publication became \"Nguoi Viet Daily News, Inc.\" in 1985. By founding the newspaper, Yen and Loan were instrumental in helping to establish all of Little Saigon in Southern California.  Their newspaper served as the flagship of the economically vibrant community and is, today, the heart of the largest Vietnamese population outside of the country of Vietnam. The headquarters of \"Nguoi Viet Daily News, Inc\" is now located in Westminster, Orange County.  (In fact, the company became such a success that other newer and smaller entities copied its name - since it was a household word - for their own non-media businesses).\n\nToday, the company boasts multiple facets, subsidiaries, and various publications, with the original seminal publication claiming a daily circulation of 20,000+ copies (Verified Audit Circulation). Copies of \"Nguoi Viet Daily News\" can be found throughout the marketplace and, in particular, most ethnic communities, and online, in bookstores, at newspaper vending machines, and Vietnamese retail venues throughout the world plus via home-delivery to residences everywhere \">{cite web|\"LAT 2019-03-21\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-col1-viet-newspaper-20190321-htmlstory.html|title=In the world famous hub of Little Saigon, Orange County, this newspaper has been giving a community a voice for 40+ years|last=Do|first=Anh|date=March 21, 2019|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|access-date=2019-04-02}}</ref>\n\n\"Nguoi Viet Daily News, Inc.\" and its founders, Yen and Loan Do, were displayed in a permanent exhibit at the historic Newseum located in Washington, D.C., and the company is responsible for various journalism endowments and scholarships.\n\nYen passed away in 2006.  Loan is retired, and serves as an informal advisor to the company.  Their adult children are spread across the continent, with their eldest an acclaimed journalist in her own right, serving in leadership capacities on many media boards and organizations, and carrying on her parents' legacy in the Golden State.\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.nguoi-viet.com/ Official News/Media/Publishing Web site of Ng\u01b0\u1eddi Vi\u1ec7t Daily News(Ng\u01b0\u1eddi Vi\u1ec7t Online - in Vietnamese)]\n* [http://www.latimes.com/news/printedition/california/la-me-yendo18aug18,1,2482663.story?coll=la-headlines-pe-california Tran, Mai & Silverstein, Stuart. (2006, August 18). ''Yen Do, 65; Publisher of First, Largest U.S. Vietnamese Paper''. The Los Angeles Times]\n\n[[Category:Media in Orange County, California]]\n[[Category:Vietnamese-American culture in California]]\n[[Category:Vietnamese-language newspapers published in California]]\n[[Category:Westminster, California]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Orange County, California]]\n[[Category:Daily newspapers published in Greater Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Publications established in 1978]]\n[[Category:1978 establishments in California]]\n", "text_old": "{{more references|date=May 2017}}\n{{infobox newspaper\n| name                 = Ng\u01b0\u1eddi Vi\u1ec7t\n| logo                 = \n| image                = Nguoi_Viet_News.jpg\n| caption              = Ng\u01b0\u1eddi Vi\u1ec7t Daily News Head Quarter\n| type                 = [[Daily newspaper]]\n| format               = Print, Digital, Online, Video, Social Media\n| status               = Active\n| owners               = ESOP\n| founder              = \u0110\u1ed7 Ng\u1ecdc Y\u1ebfn\n| publisher 